      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/api/inventory/NetworkCmProxyInventoryFacade.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 183,
      "message": "The YangModelCmHandle here has the info we need, so pass it to the applyCurrentTrustLevel method:\n\n    final YangModelCmHandle inventoryPersistence.getYangModelCmHandle(cmHandleId);\n    final NcmpServiceCmHandle ncmpServiceCmHandle = YangDataConverter.toNcmpServiceCmHandle(yangModelCmHandle);\n    final String dmiServiceName = yangModelCmHandle.resolveDmiServiceName(DATA);\n    applyCurrentTrustLevel(ncmpServiceCmHandle, dmiServiceName);",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-08-22 16:37:41.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "bf059692_6ace61ba",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/api/inventory/NetworkCmProxyInventoryFacade.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 210,
      "message": "Just wondering, why has this changed to effective trust level where it wasn't before? Was that a bug? If so, it should really be done in a different Jira ticket.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
